FBIS3-57071 "drsov015_v_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 Lithuania Defense Minister Cited on Defense Appropriations PM2101113994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 21 Jan 94 p 1 PM2101113994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Report by Valeriy Gromak under "News" rubric: "If We Had the Money, Would We Buy Ourselves a Defense Capability?"] [Text] Vilnius -- Budget appropriations for Lithuanian territorial defense needs in 1994 will remain proportionally unchanged compared to last year, comprising 4.6 percent of the budget. However, the size of these appropriations has increased 60 percent and stands at 130 million litai (approximately $33 million). This was announced by Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius. National Defense Minister Linas Linkevicius is sure that, despite these meager budget appropriations, the country will be able to establish a defense system that befits our membership of international security structures.
